# bin/

Intent CLI shell script implementations. Contains the executable entry point (`intent`), shared configuration and helper libraries (`intent_config`, `intent_helpers`), and specialized subcommands for steel thread management, project initialization, auditing, and documentation workflows.

## Files

- `intent` -- Main entry point and command dispatcher
- `intent_main` -- Backward compatibility wrapper (legacy stp command)
- `intent_minimal` -- Lightweight minimal wrapper for early-phase testing
- `intent_helpers` -- Shared utility functions (version, checksums, terminal width, JSON parsing)
- `intent_config` -- JSON config loading, project root detection, configuration hierarchy
- `intent_init` -- Initialize new Intent projects with directory structure
- `intent_bootstrap` -- First-time Intent setup and global configuration
- `intent_upgrade` -- Migrate STP/Intent projects to latest version
- `intent_st` -- Create, list, edit, repair steel threads (directory-based)
- `intent_wp` -- Manage work packages within steel threads
- `intent_st_zero` -- Retrofit ST0000 deliverables into brownfield projects
- `intent_plugin` -- Discover and list installed Intent plugins
- `intent_ext` -- Manage user extensions at ~/.intent/ext/ with manifest validation
- `intent_organise` -- Organize steel threads by status into subdirectories
- `intent_audit` -- Automated code quality checks via Credo (Elixir)
- `intent_modules` -- MODULES.md registry enforcement and guardrails
- `intent_treeindex` -- Generate .treeindex directory summaries via Claude AI
- `intent_fileindex` -- Create and maintain file indexes with checkbox state tracking
- `intent_learn` -- Capture footguns/patterns to .intent/learnings.md
- `intent_llm` -- Display LLM guidance and usage rules
- `intent_info` -- Show Intent installation and project status
- `intent_help` -- Command-specific help and general usage
- `intent_doctor` -- Diagnose and fix configuration issues
